body_html:
I updated my tensorflow from version 1.4.0 to 1.11.0. After that, when I tried "import tensorflow as tf", I ran into following problem:

File "C:\Users\MyName\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python36\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\python\pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py", line 96, in
TFE_NewContextOptions = _pywrap_tensorflow_internal.TFE_NewContextOptions
AttributeError: module '_pywrap_tensorflow_internal' has no attribute 'TFE_NewContextOptions'

May I know if you could give me any clue to sort this out? Thanks!

body:
I updated my tensorflow from version 1.4.0 to 1.11.0. After that, when I tried "import tensorflow as tf", I ran into following problem:

File "C:\Users\MyName\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python36\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\python\pywrap_tensorflow_internal.py", line 96, in <module>
    TFE_NewContextOptions = _pywrap_tensorflow_internal.TFE_NewContextOptions
AttributeError: module '_pywrap_tensorflow_internal' has no attribute 'TFE_NewContextOptions'

May I know if you could give me any clue to sort this out? Thanks!
